# Sovereign AI Technical Book Specification
# First BookForge Publication from DanielKliewer.com Knowledge Graph

id: sovereign-ai-book
title: Sovereign AI - A Technical Guide to Local-First Intelligent Systems
version: 1.0.0
status: implemented
purpose: >
  Synthesize the DanielKliewer.com knowledge graph into a comprehensive technical
  book covering Sovereign AI, Knowledge Graphs, Dynamic Persona MoE RAG, Context
  Engineering, Agentic Systems, and related research. The book will serve as both
  a practical guide and theoretical foundation for building local-first intelligent
  systems that prioritize sovereignty, privacy, and deterministic behavior.

requirements:
  - Book must cover Sovereign AI principles and implementation patterns
  - Book must explain Knowledge Graph construction and utilization
  - Book must detail Dynamic Persona MoE RAG architecture
  - Book must address Context Engineering techniques and best practices
  - Book must describe Agentic System design and coordination
  - Book must include practical examples and implementation guidance
  - Book must maintain technical accuracy throughout
  - Book must provide evidence-backed claims and recommendations
  - Book must be internally consistent across chapters
  - Book must include technical illustrations for complex concepts
  - Book must support multiple output formats (PDF, EPUB, HTML)
  - Book must be updatable when knowledge base evolves

constraints:
  - Content must be synthesized from knowledge graph, not copied from blog posts
  - Every claim must trace to evidence in the knowledge graph or external sources
  - Technical examples must be functional and reproducible
  - Illustrations must be generated from structured specifications
  - Book must not require external API calls for core content generation
  - Publication must be achievable with local LLM inference via Ollama
  - All chapters must undergo technical and editorial review
  - Book structure must follow the BookForge pipeline

acceptance_criteria:
  - Given knowledge graph from DanielKliewer.com, system produces complete book blueprint
  - Given book blueprint, system generates all chapter specifications with evidence maps
  - Given chapter specifications, system generates technically accurate chapters
  - Given generated chapters, system produces review reports with actionable feedback
  - Given reviewed content, system compiles to PDF, EPUB, and HTML formats
  - Given knowledge graph updates, system identifies and regenerates affected chapters
  - Given any chapter, system can trace every paragraph to supporting evidence
  - Given complex concepts, system generates appropriate technical illustrations
  - Given the complete book, system produces glossary and index
  - Given final compilation, system generates publication-ready documents

api_specification:
  endpoints:
    - path: /api/book/sovereign-ai/import
      method: POST
      request:
        body:
          source_path: string (required)
          include_external: boolean
      response:
        200:
          book_id: string
          graph_stats: object
          topic_coverage: array

    - path: /api/book/sovereign-ai/survey
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          book_id: string (required)
      response:
        200:
          survey_results: object
          major_concepts: array
          knowledge_gaps: array

    - path: /api/book/sovereign-ai/structure
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          book_id: string (required)
          style: string (optional)
      response:
        200:
          structure_id: string
          parts: array
          chapters: array

    - path: /api/book/sovereign-ai/chapters
      method: GET
      request:
        params:
          book_id: string (required)
          chapter_id: string (optional)
      response:
        200:
          chapters: array
          chapter_details: object

    - path: /api/book/sovereign-ai/generate
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          book_id: string (required)
          chapter_id: string (required)
          style: string (optional)
      response:
        200:
          generation_id: string
          chapter_content: string
          word_count: integer
          citations: array

    - path: /api/book/sovereign-ai/review
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          book_id: string (required)
          chapter_id: string (required)
          review_types: array (required)
      response:
        200:
          review_reports: array
          overall_score: float
          revision_needed: boolean

    - path: /api/book/sovereign-ai/compile
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          book_id: string (required)
          formats: array (required)
          include_assets: boolean
      response:
        200:
          compilation_id: string
          output_files: array
          total_pages: integer

data_models:
  - name: BookProject
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique book project identifier
      - name: title
        type: string
        description: Book title
      - name: knowledge_graph_id
        type: string
        description: Source knowledge graph
      - name: status
        type: string
        description: Current pipeline stage
      - name: created_at
        type: datetime
        description: Project creation timestamp
      - name: updated_at
        type: datetime
        description: Last update timestamp

  - name: TopicCoverage
    fields:
      - name: topic
        type: string
        description: Topic or concept name
      - name: coverage_score
        type: float
        description: Coverage completeness (0-1)
      - name: chapter_references
        type: array
        description: Chapters covering this topic
      - name: evidence_count
        type: integer
        description: Supporting evidence pieces

  - name: KnowledgeGap
    fields:
      - name: topic
        type: string
        description: Identified knowledge gap
      - name: importance
        type: string
        description: Gap importance (critical, important, minor)
      - name: research_sources
        type: array
        description: Potential research sources
      - name: resolution_strategy
        type: string
        description: How to address the gap

  - name: BookStructure
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique structure identifier
      - name: parts
        type: array
        description: High-level book divisions
      - name: chapters
        type: array
        description: Detailed chapter specifications
      - name: learning_path
        type: array
        description: Recommended reading order

  - name: ChapterContent
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique chapter identifier
      - name: title
        type: string
        description: Chapter title
      - name: content
        type: string
        description: Chapter markdown content
      - name: word_count
        type: integer
        description: Chapter word count
      - name: citations
        type: array
        description: Inline citations
      - name: illustrations
        type: array
        description: Technical figures

  - name: ReviewReport
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique review identifier
      - name: chapter_id
        type: string
        description: Chapter being reviewed
      - name: reviewer_type
        type: string
        description: Type of reviewer
      - name: findings
        type: array
        description: Review findings
      - name: recommendations
        type: array
        description: Improvement suggestions
      - name: score
        type: float
        description: Quality score

test_cases:
  - id: import_danielkliewer_knowledge_graph
    name: import_danielkliewer_knowledge_graph
    description: Import DanielKliewer.com knowledge graph
    given: DanielKliewer.com knowledge graph export
    when: POST /api/book/sovereign-ai/import
    then: 200 with book_id and topic coverage analysis

  - id: survey_identifies_sovereign_ai_concepts
    name: survey_identifies_sovereign_ai_concepts
    description: Survey identifies Sovereign AI concepts
    given: Imported knowledge graph
    when: POST /api/book/sovereign-ai/survey
    then: 200 with Sovereign AI, KG, MoE RAG, Context Engineering concepts

  - id: structure_creates_coherent_parts
    name: structure_creates_coherent_parts
    description: Create coherent book structure
    given: Survey results
    when: POST /api/book/sovereign-ai/structure
    then: 200 with logical book parts and chapter flow

  - id: chapter_generation_with_evidence
    name: chapter_generation_with_evidence
    description: Generate chapter with evidence
    given: Chapter specification with evidence sources
    when: POST /api/book/sovereign-ai/generate
    then: 200 with technical content and citations

  - id: technical_review_validates_accuracy
    name: technical_review_validates_accuracy
    description: Technical review validates accuracy
    given: Generated chapter
    when: POST /api/book/sovereign-ai/review
    then: 200 with technical accuracy assessment

  - id: editorial_review_enhances_readability
    name: editorial_review_enhances_readability
    description: Editorial review enhances readability
    given: Generated chapter
    when: POST /api/book/sovereign-ai/review
    then: 200 with editorial improvements

  - id: multi_format_output_generation
    name: multi_format_output_generation
    description: Generate multi-format output
    given: Reviewed and finalized book
    when: POST /api/book/sovereign-ai/compile
    then: 200 with PDF, EPUB, HTML files

  - id: incremental_update_on_new_content
    name: incremental_update_on_new_content
    description: Incremental update on new content
    given: New knowledge graph content
    when: System processes updates
    then: Only affected chapters regenerated

  - id: glossary_and_index_generation
    name: glossary_and_index_generation
    description: Generate glossary and index
    given: Complete book content
    when: System generates supplementary materials
    then: Comprehensive glossary and index created

  - id: publication_quality_output
    name: publication_quality_output
    description: Generate publication quality output
    given: Final compiled book
    when: User opens output files
    then: Professional publication quality achieved

references:
  - title: DanielKliewer.com Knowledge Graph
    url: https://danielkliewer.com
  - title: Sovereign AI Research
    url: https://arxiv.org/search/?query=sovereign+AI
  - title: Knowledge Graph Construction
    url: https://www.w3.org/wiki/Graphs_-_Knowledge_Graph
  - title: MoE Architecture Research
    url: https://arxiv.org/search/?query=mixture+of+experts
  - title: Context Engineering Principles
    url: https://www.promptingguide.ai/techniques/contextengineering

implementation_notes: >
  This specification defines the first concrete implementation of BookForge:
  a comprehensive technical book synthesized from DanielKliewer.com's knowledge
  graph. The book covers six major themes: Sovereign AI principles, Knowledge
  Graph construction and utilization, Dynamic Persona MoE RAG architecture,
  Context Engineering techniques, Agentic System design, and Future AI
  Architectures. Each theme becomes a book part containing multiple chapters.
  The runtime will use BookForge's pipeline to survey the knowledge graph,
  discover concepts, construct themes, build blueprint, generate chapter
  specifications with evidence maps, create technical illustrations, generate
  chapters with citations, and compile to multiple formats. All content must
  be synthesized from the knowledge graph rather than copied from original
  blog posts. The system will track provenance for every paragraph and
  support incremental updates as the knowledge base evolves.